The Nigeria Immigration Service (NIS) has announced the death of one of its officers, Deputy Controller General (DCG) Raymond Tonye Akrah, who passed away on June 9, 2018 The late DCG, according to Mohammed Babandede, the Comptroller General (DG), was until his demise the Head of the Directorate of Border Management at the Immigration headquarters, Abuja. He died after a brief. A statement personally signed by the Immigration boss says that the late DCG, who hailed from Opobo Town in Rivers State, was born on December 11, 1960. The late Jaja attended University of Nigeria, Nsukka, (UNN) where he studied Political Science. He joined the NIS in 1985 as an Assistant Superintendent of Immigration (ASI), and subsequently attended so many internal and international courses, including the Command and Staff College Sokoto, Institute of Security Studies where he was a Fellow, Infantry Centre and School in Jaji amongst others. He was promoted to the rank of Deputy Comptroller General of Immigration in 2017 and was deployed to head the newly restructured Directorate of Border Management, a position he held until his demise. Babandede described late Jaja as jolly fellow and gentleman, whom he said would be remembered for his high sense of discipline and uncommon loyalty to constituted authorities. No date has been fixed for his burial. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 